  "text": "we notice that the rates in Proposition 1 are very similar to those in Bai (2004, Theorem 6 for the case d < q and Theorem 4 for the case d = q). In other words, the QML estimator converges at the same rate than the estimator based on PC on the levels, which resembles the result in [CITATION_1] for the stationary case. However, in the simulation study in Section 5 show that our estimator behave much better in finite samples.",
